==========================================================
STEP 1
BUILDING THE NETWORK NODES
==========================================================

Nodes are the physical and logical entities.

Example:

    Subnets: DMZ, Internal, Database
    Servers: Web-01, App-01, DB-Primary

The database creates these as isolated islands.


==========================================================
STEP 2
CONNECTING THE RELATIONSHIPS
==========================================================

We map out how data flows through the network.

Example:

    Web-01  ---[CAN_REACH]--->  App-01
    App-01  ---[CAN_REACH]--->  DB-Primary

This creates "Lateral Movement Paths." If a hacker breaches 
Web-01, we now mathematically know they have a path to the 
Database.


==========================================================
STEP 3
INJECTING VULNERABILITIES (CVEs)
==========================================================

We take real-world MITRE ATT&CK Vulnerabilities:

Example:

    CVE-2017-0144 (EternalBlue)
    CVE-2021-44228 (Log4Shell)

We attach these vulnerabilities directly to the servers 
that are exposed to them.


==========================================================
STEP 4
AI EMBEDDING (GRAPHRAG)
==========================================================

Model Used:

    SentenceTransformer (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)

The AI reads the text description of the vulnerability:
"Log4Shell allows remote code execution..."

And converts it into a 384-dimensional mathematical vector:
[0.012, -0.453, 0.991, ...]

Purpose:

    When Phase 4 asks "Find me vulnerabilities similar to 
    remote execution", Neo4j can instantly search these 
    vectors using Cosine Similarity.


